  "response": "As an AI, I don't experience interviews or personal interactions, but I can share examples of unusual questions that interviewers sometimes ask to gauge creativity, problem-solving, and personality. Here are a few examples:\n\n1. If you were an animal, what would you be and why?\n2. How would you sell ice in Antarctica?\n3. If you could have dinner with any three people, dead or alive, who would they be?\n4. How many basketballs can fit in this room?\n5. If you were a crayon, what color would you be and why?\n\nThese questions are typically used to see how candidates think on their feet and to give insight into their personalities.",
